place.name: WOODBASTWICK
place.gazetteerText: WOODBASTWICK, a parish, with a village, in Blofield district, Norfolk; 4¼ miles N by E of Brundall r. station, and 8 NE by E of Norwich. It has a post-office under Norwich. Acres, 2,163. Real property, £2,685. Pop., 294. Houses, 50. W. Hall is the seat of A. Cator, Esq. The living is a vicarage, united with Panxworth, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £206.* Patron, A. Cator, Esq. The church is good. Charities, £8. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
